# The service needs no credentials of its own: hosts authenticate with their own
# Navidrome accounts. The only settings are where Navidrome lives and what address
# to listen on. For the Docker deployment set these in docker-compose.yml instead;
# these variables are read when running the binary directly.
#
# LISTEN_ADDR=:8080
# ND_URL=http://localhost:4533

# --- Transcoding ------------------------------------------------------------
# Every track is streamed through Navidrome's transcoder so each listener gets a
# predictable, bandwidth-capped stream instead of the original (possibly
# lossless) file. STREAM_FORMAT must name a transcoding profile that exists in
# Navidrome; STREAM_MAX_BITRATE is the cap in kbps (0 = no cap, let the profile
# decide). For the Docker deployment, docker-compose.yml reads these same names
# from this file (copy it to .env); for the bare binary, export them.
#
# Whether a stream is VBR or CBR is decided by the Navidrome profile you pick
# here, not by this service:
#
#   - mp3  : Navidrome's stock profile is CBR. Universally compatible (all
#            browsers incl. Safari/iOS). This is the default.
#   - opus : ships with Navidrome and is VBR by default (libopus treats the
#            bitrate as a VBR target). Best quality-per-byte. Caveat: Safari
#            plays Ogg/Opus unreliably, so avoid it if guests use Safari/iOS.
#   - a custom VBR MP3 profile you add in Navidrome (e.g. named "mp3 vbr" with
#            an `-q:a` ffmpeg command) — then set STREAM_FORMAT to its name.
#   - raw  : no transcoding; serve the original files.
#
# Default (active): 256 kbps CBR MP3.
# STREAM_FORMAT=mp3
# STREAM_MAX_BITRATE=256
#
# VBR, smaller files (uncomment to use Opus; check Safari/iOS first):
# STREAM_FORMAT=opus
# STREAM_MAX_BITRATE=128
#
# Original quality, no transcoding:
# STREAM_FORMAT=raw
# STREAM_MAX_BITRATE=0
